description:
What happened to Kris Kremers and Lisanne Froon?
An update and complete overview with a brand-new theory which might explain most of the mysteries which keep haunting this case.

This video is intended to provoke discussions and all comments are very welcome. To join the discussion, please log in to Reddit r/KremersFroon.
fulltitle: What happened to Kris Kremers and Lisanne Froon?

comments.text: I don't think the girls were writing down supplies twice a day to prevent eachother from cheating
comments.author: @CC-xn5xi

comments.text: Good job!!!! Nicely done!! Many, many thanks!

i have been following this case on and off since pre-covid times, and it has always fascinated me, but also made me feel so bad because of what they must have felt while they were lost- the fear is unimaginable. i have read countless theories and while i have always leaned toward foul play, i recently started to read more and more about the accident theory, and i think this video seals it for me. if it turns out there's a degree of foul play involved i wouldn't be surprised, but damn. this is by far the most well-researched and detailed video about this case that i watched. the amount of work in it must be crazy. i know it's all technically a theory and may never be officially proven, but it's definitely the most realistic way of events, my jaw dropped when you mentioned the moon rays and how the photos were taken seconds before moonset... it's so crazy to think about, but it makes so much sense. thank you for the amazing upload, and may Kris and Lisanne rest easy.
comments.author: @szertralin

comments.text:
I followed this case from the beginning. This video gives me the first reasonable explanation why the girls would have left the trail. It seems almost logic that what you describe and conclude may have happened exactly like this. They avoided the 2nd bridge (maybe because of bad ecperience at the first bridge) and went upstream looking for the best.location to cross the river. At the 2nd bridge the stream was too rough and they probably knew the river between the 1st and 2nd bridge. They made the crossing and wanted to hit the trail at the 2nd bridge by going down the riverside at the opposite side of the trail. Sounds reasonable. Their injuries may have been caused at the 1st cable bridge, during the wading through the river or while reaching the last location. I imagine they jumped or slid down between those big boulders of the night location.
Your videos are well done. The night location will be found soon. Thanks for this.
